{
  "text": "CBA/Ca (H-2 k ), C57BL/6 (B6, H-2 b ), BALB/c (H-2 d ) and C3H/HeJ (H-2 k ) mice were bred and maintained in a pathogen-free facility at the Medical College of Georgia. Transgenic HLA-G mice (on a CBA/Ca background) carry a recombinant H-2K b /HLA-G gene expressed in all cells and have been described previously [CITATION_1] . Two independent lineages of homozygous transgenic mice (designated T1 and T3 mice) were established by mating sibling transgenic mice. Homozygous mice from both lines were used for these experiments and results were identical.",
